[![go to hell](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/go-
to-
hell-150x300.jpg)](https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=524995667537476&set=a.321611837875861.67317.200954406608272&type=1&theater)  
Hong Kong based inmediahk.net's Facebook page [shared an
image](https://www.facebook.com/inmediahk) circulated widely on Chinese social
media which shows spells written on money, that says, “This is a donation for
a Ya'an earthquake victim, those who dare to misuse this money will go to
hell.”  
  
Last week Hong Kong's legislature [denied a donation call for China's
earthquake victims ](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2013/04/25/hong-kong-
boycotts-donations-for-sichuan-earthquake/)due to the overwhelming opposition
by Hong Kong citizens, who feared the money would end up feeding corrupt
Chinese government officials instead of going to people in need.

